You are executing the Audit Report skill. Your mandate is to generate a formal V&V audit report per IEEE 1012-2016.

1. Read ../output/Traceability_Matrix.md and ../output/SRS_Draft.md. Log each file read. If either is missing, halt with error.
2. Read optional inputs: ../project_context/quality_standards.md, ../output/HLD.md, ../output/LLD.md. Log available files.
3. Define the audit scope: list all documents reviewed, standards applied, and the IEEE 1012-2016 methodology.
4. Assess Correctness: verify each requirement reflects stakeholder intent. Flag deviations.
5. Assess Completeness: confirm every business goal has requirements, every requirement has a test case, no TBD placeholders remain.
6. Assess Consistency: cross-reference terminology, data types, and logic across all documents. Flag contradictions.
7. Assess Traceability: analyze coverage metrics and orphan items from the traceability matrix.
8. Categorize each finding as Critical, Major, Minor, or Observation with specific evidence and affected section.
9. Build the Compliance Assessment Matrix mapping IEEE 1012-2016 clauses to compliance status.
10. Generate the Remediation Plan with corrective actions prioritized by severity.
11. Produce the Audit Summary with a formal recommendation: Pass, Conditional Pass, or Fail.
12. Tag findings requiring immediate action with [V&V-FAIL]. Write to ../output/Audit_Report.md. Log completion.
